Cell["Schwinger\[CloseCurlyQuote]s Boson representation of spin 1/2", \
"ExampleText",
 CellFrame->{{0, 0}, {0, 0.5}},
 CellID->1157609157,ExpressionUUID->"a680492a-adc3-47ed-b311-a7a8f88ff557"],

Cell["\<\
In physics, bosons can only have integer spins, but in non-relativistic \
theories, the spin-statistics theorem does not apply and one can think of \
bosons with half-integer spins. Of course, in such cases, the \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]spin\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] does not refer to real \
spins but to pseudo-spins or even to any other quantum numbers that have \
nothing to do with spins.\
\>", "ExampleText",
 CellID->1882743526,ExpressionUUID->"f2908ed7-a739-4ce0-b6f2-ce61be388846"],

Cell["\<\
For this reason,  the package gives you a warning and yet still obeys you to \
define bosons with half-integer spin.\
\>", "ExampleText",
 CellID->98902937,ExpressionUUID->"193428b8-ef28-427f-ae75-20140e0f3f4a"],

